examples.en: We drew down our cash reserves.
Crude oil reserves are running down.
The President has activated the reserves.
The management reserves the right to refuse admission.
Technically, a bank's reserves belong to the stockholders.
Huge imports were draining the country's currency reserves.
He had to call upon his inner reserves of strength to keep going.
He estimates that current oil reserves are 20 percent lower than they were a year ago.
Nature reserves were set up around new power stations to mollify local conservationists.
According to government estimates, current oil reserves are 10 percent lower than they were a year ago.
